# data/library.jsonl — curated MacAtrium source dataset (UTF-8 JSONL, PR-friendly).
#
# Compiled into the on-Mac metadata/catalog.jsonl by `atrium catalog`
# (tools/atrium-tool), which DERIVES the many-to-many `categories` from the
# facet fields below — the "facets + decade buckets" model (docs/06):
#   kind  -> Games | Applications | Utilities
#   genre -> verbatim genre categories
#   color -> "Color" / "B&W"
#   year  -> a decade bucket ("1980s" / "1990s"); raw year kept for sort
#   vendor-> the publisher (Broderbund, ...)
#   mouse -> "Mouse Required" / "No Mouse"
#
# Lines starting with '#' or '//', and blank lines, are ignored.
# `app` paths are relative to the /MacAtrium root on the target volume.
# Titles here are real Macintosh classics present in the MacPack collection;
# treat the metadata as a curated starter — refine vendor/year/etc. via PR.
